{"id":33164,"title":"History of treatment of conjoined twins.","abstract":"This paper presents a history of the treatment of conjoined twins. The first mention of this malformation comes from the Neolithic period. Conjoined twins were depicted in mythologies of ancient peoples. The present paper focuses on the theories of formation of Siamese twins and attempts at their separation. Moreover, the history of treatment of conjoined twins in Poland is described.","date":"2014-05-26","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24858972","annotations":[{"name":"Neolithic","weight":0.838145,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neolithic"},{"name":"Mythology","weight":0.646519,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mythology"},{"name":"Poland","weight":0.444669,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poland"},{"name":"Theory","weight":0.429207,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theory"},{"name":"Paper","weight":0.307909,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paper"},{"name":"Conjoined twins","weight":0.297222,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conjoined_twins"},{"name":"History","weight":0.18053,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History"},{"name":"Ancient history","weight":0.101782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ancient_history"},{"name":"Congenital disorder","weight":0.0424182,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congenital_disorder"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.0185779,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Formation (stratigraphy)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Formation_(stratigraphy)"},{"name":"Twin","weight":0.0159005,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twin"},{"name":"Thai people","weight":0.0157947,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thai_people"},{"name":"Sep